# Monorepo Architecture Guide

This project follows a monorepo architecture using Turborepo and PNPM workspaces.

## Workspace Structure

The project is organized into separate packages to maintain clear separation of concerns:

```
lol-assistant/
├── apps/               # Frontend applications
│   ├── web/            # Vite-based web app
│   └── nextjs/         # Next.js application
├── packages/           # Shared libraries & modules
│   ├── api/            # API integrations
│   ├── db/             # Database layer (Prisma)
│   ├── ui/             # Shared UI components
│   ├── cron-scripts/   # Background tasks  
│   └── ...
│
└── api/                # Serverless functions (for Vercel)
    └── crons/          # Cron job endpoints
```

## Package Dependencies

- Packages can depend on each other using the workspace protocol: `"@lol-assistant/ui": "workspace:*"`
- Always use the same version of shared dependencies across packages

## Scripts Execution

- From the root: `pnpm dev` - Start all apps in development mode
- For specific packages: `pnpm --filter @lol-assistant/web dev`
- For cron scripts: `pnpm --filter @lol-assistant/cron-scripts run start sample-script`

## Deployment

- Frontend apps are deployed separately
- Cron jobs use Vercel Serverless Functions with endpoints in `api/crons/`
